Choose among

1: Density Specific heat Conductivity INDEPENDENT of TIME & TEMP
if CAPACITY, CONDUCTIVITY, HEAT TRANSFER COEFFICIENT are
   INDEPENDENT of TIME and TEMPERATURE
and if SOURCES and CONTACTS depend ONLY of TIME (Not TEMPERATURE)

2: At least one SOURCE & CONTACT is DEPENDENT of TIME & TEMP
if CAPACITY, CONDUCTIVITY, HEAT TRANSFER COEFFICIENT are
   INDEPENDENT of TIME and TEMPERATURE
and if SOURCES and CONTACTS depend of TIME and TEMPERATURE


3: At least one COEFFICIENT DEPENDENT of TIME & TEMPERATURE
if ONE of the HEAT COEFFICIENTS are DEPENDENT of TIME & TEMPERATURE

Remark:
The second option requires fix point iterations
on the second member and the matrices are constants.

The third option requires fix point iterations with
a computation of the matrices for each iteration
=> important cost
